JsExtensionPackage
==================

Includes the following tools

js_navigation_helpers (Navigation helpers builds navigation bar)
js_custom_helpers (Include some custom helpers)
js_flash_extension (For translation and assigning flash error, notice and success.)


I included one plugin inside my plugin, I used allot to make small helpers extension for my views.
block_helpers => http://github.com/markevans/block_helpers/tree/master

Example
=======

js_navigation_extension
=======================

Code:
<% navigation(:class => "login") do |n| %>
	<%= n.l("Signup", :action => "signup") %>
	<%= n.l("Forgot Password", :action => "forgot_password") %>
<% end %>

Result:
<ul class="login">
	<li><a href="/user/signup">Signup</a></li>
	<li><a href="/user/forgot_password">Forgot Password</a></li>
</ul>


js_custom_helpers
=================

Code:
<%= flash_messages %>

Result: (depends on which flash hash is not blank):
<div class="flash flash-error">...message..</div>

Code:
<%= link_back %>

Result:
<a href=""javascript:history.go(-1)">Back</a>

Code:
<%= link_popup('Terms of service', :action => "terms") %>

Result:
<a href="/user/terms" onclick="window.open(this.href,'new_window_name','height=300,width=600,toolbar=no,location=no,directories=no,status=no,menubar=no,scrollbars=yes,resizable=yes');return false;">Terms of service</a>


